Mitsubishi Corp. (8058) , Innovation
Network Corp. of Japan and Solar Ventures acquired  Italy â€™s Solar
Holding S.R.L for an undisclosed amount.  Mitsubishi bought 50 percent of the power producer,
Innovation Network 35 percent and Solar Ventures the rest, the
Japanese trading company said in a statement today.  Solar Holding, a unit of Solar Ventures S.R.L., has the
capacity to produce 42 megawatts of power across 19 sites in
Italy, which are already managed by Solar Ventures.  Mitsubishi will spend 3 billion yen ($31.4 million) and
Innovation Network will invest 2 billion yen to buy Solar
Holding, The Nikkei newspaper reported today, without saying how
it obtained the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
